Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.messages

Class OperationMessage

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.messages.OperationMessage
All Implemented Interfaces:
Message, Triaged, Transmittable, Named, AsString, StringFormattable
Direct Known Subclasses:
OperationLifecycleMessage, OperationStatusMessage
public abstract class OperationMessage extends Object implements Named, Message
Base implementation of the Message interface. Represents a message destined for a Listener such as a Logger with arguments which can be interpolated if the message is formatted with formatted(MessageFormat[]). All OperationMessages have the attributes defined in Message.

For messages that might be sent to frequently, maximumFrequency(Frequency) can be used to specify that the receiver only handle the message every so often. Logs support this feature, so it is possible to easily tag a message as something to only log once in a while.

    • maximumFrequency

      public Frequency maximumFrequency()
      Returns the frequency with which this message should be logged or null if the message should always be logged.

      NOTE: Message identity is determined by looking at the un-formatted message returned by message(). If message() does not return a constant string, a bounded map error may occur as the system attempts to track too many message frequencies.
